definition: to obliterate (some words, or part of a picture etc) using correction fluid, ink, paint etc/to paint out/to paint over
to apply (paint etc)/to smear/to daub/to blot out/to scribble/to scrawl/(literary) mud/street

to go/to go to (a place)/(of a time etc) last/just passed/to send/to remove/to get rid of/to reduce/to be apart from in space or time/to die (euphemism)/to play (a part)/(when used either before or after a verb) to go in order to do sth/(after a verb of motion indicates movement away from the speaker)/(used after certain verbs to indicate detachment or separation)

sentences.english: Can you white out those letters at the edge of the page?
sentences.chinese: 你能用塗改液塗去這一頁邊上的這些字母嗎？

sentences.english: Please ink out the following passage.
sentences.chinese: 請把下一段用墨水塗去。

sentences.english: We paint the scratching on the wall out.
sentences.chinese: 我們用油漆塗去牆上亂畫的東西。

sentences.english: I obliterate the word with chalk.
sentences.chinese: 我用粉筆把這個單詞塗去了。

sentences.english: Some words were blacked out in this line.
sentences.chinese: 這一行裏有幾個字被塗去了。

sentences.english: Could you use the correction fluid to alter the letter on the page.
sentences.chinese: 你能用塗改液塗去這一頁邊上的這些字母嗎？

sentences.english: He has inked out the mistakes in the typescript.
sentences.chinese: 他已用墨水塗去了打字稿中的錯誤。

sentences.english: He obliterated two words in ink / with a pen.
sentences.chinese: 他用鋼筆把那兩個單詞塗去了。

sentences.english: And he began applying the pearly , gluey mess to her inky cheeks.
sentences.chinese: 說着便抓起豆泥蓮蓉珍珠糊，往她臉上塗去。
